03/03/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- A homemade bomb exploded early Monday (March 3rd) in front of the building housing the forestry directorate, part of the ministry of environment, planning and public work in Athens. 
About 20 minutes before the blast, a caller phoned in a warning to the Eleftherotypia newspaper. 
The blast broke windows, but no injuries were reported. 
(Sky, AP - 03/03/08)
